RXZ-vwRFi4S2biIiCY", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/entity_urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAoiE18B78o1bNpS5FyYNG_eMhrBY_O8z0A", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/first_name": "Ena", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/follower_count": "2338", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/headline": "Director of Operations ", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/last_name": "Roy", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/premium": "false", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/profile_picture": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/C4D03AQHEcSCPJMtlEQ/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/0/1610677760791?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=kCaijd78R0uEENpWjQ2yEr7YVPyQmJX4vmBSAxr6mk0", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/public_identifier": "ena-roy-87bb2648", "peopleAlsoViewed/24/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAAAoiE18B78o1bNpS5FyYNG_eMhrBY_O8z0A", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/entity_urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAABMYr4BAnJkJQ9HzF4bnyTcDdHObxaoKHY", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/first_name": "Patrick", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/follower_count": "1088", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/headline": "Multi Property Hotel Manager at Marriott International", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/last_name": "Smekens", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/premium": "false", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/profile_picture": "https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/v2/D5603AQGJEruO8k0ZOg/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/profile-displayphoto-shrink_800_800/0/1689574971678?e=1778112000&v=beta&t=m4IxHjTJiG5rzP0yB8Vdjn3RGhARiTiJ3hdbo_7MeAY", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/public_identifier": "patrick-smekens-bba8141", "peopleAlsoViewed/25/url": "https://linkedin.com/in/ACoAAABMYr4BAnJkJQ9HzF4bnyTcDdHObxaoKHY", "publicIdentifier": "arjun-channa-85040321", "recommendations/0/context": "Arjun was senior to Inês but didn't manage Inês directly", "recommendations/0/date": "May 8, 2025", "recommendations/0/description": "To who ever is reading this: \n\nIn the short time that I’ve known Ines, I’ve come to admire her passion and drive to get the best outcome of every task. \n\nShe was instrumental in the launch of RIZZ and internal project combining food fashion and art event in 2024. That’s where I really noticed how she can drive sales and teams alike. \n\nI realize her potential and she will go places. ", "recommendations/0/name": "Inês Adelino", "recommendations/0/subtitle": "Hotelier | Sales and Marketing Manager at Hyatt | Les Roches Alumni", "recommendations/0/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/inês-adelino-9b4625180/", "recommendations/0/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAACrOkVgBJeA0MxGcCREuFwi2lyErngAxh-w", "recommendations/1/context": "Arjun worked with Georgina but they were at different companies", "recommendations/1/date": "November 20, 2024", "recommendations/1/description": "To whomsoever this may concern - I’ve had the privilege to work alongside Ms Georgina Govin on several complex projects during my tenure as General Manager at The Ritz-Carlton. \n\nGeorgina displayed the highest order of meticulous planning, timely communication and flawless execution. Connecting with contractors on behalf of our team to get things done in a manner that would cause the least disruption to our Ladies & Gentlemen and of course our Guests. \n\nIf the above was not enough, each visit to the hotel, she made meaningful connections with all our team members, something that always goes the extra mile. \n\nThank you Georgina and I wish you the very best in your incredible journey ahead. ", "recommendations/1/name": "Georgina Govin", "recommendations/1/subtitle": "Owner’s side representation, consulting, and management of capital vertical construction projects and programs.", "recommendations/1/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/georginagovin/", "recommendations/1/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAADT8gUBaLiw0ngRXCK1ps6M5DVIDAMRUHE", "recommendations/2/context": "Arjun was senior to Zdravko but didn't manage Zdravko directly", "recommendations/2/date": "May 14, 2024", "recommendations/2/description": "To whom sober it may concern \n\nZdravko - better known as Dr Z, both internally by Associates but equally externally by Guests/Patrons is a Gentleman of Gentlemen and a true thoughtful professional. \n\nI would answer ‘yes’ without blink of an eye before the end of the question ‘would you hire Dr Z again in your establishment’? \n\nDr Z is a fine professional who examples the core values of hospitality to the fullest and in the most consistent manner I’ve ever witnessed in my career across the globe. \n\nHe leads with his heart but equally a thoughtful mind. \n\nEach banquet event I’ve witnessed under his leadership has had cleverly planted strategies proactively planted to win the client over. \n\nDuring my tenure as proud General Manager of The Westin Calgary I’ve personally received numerous complimentary notes from our Guests commending Dr Z’s attention to detail and flawless execution to fulfill their needs during an event. \n\nI’m extremely privileged to have served Dr Z and will never hesitate to recommend him \n\nThank you Dr Z - you are truly one of a kind \n\nBest regards \n\nArjun Channa ", "recommendations/2/name": "Zdravko Andric", "recommendations/2/subtitle": "Banquet Team Leader at The Westin Calgary", "recommendations/2/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/zdravko-andric-71787a13/", "recommendations/2/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAALMToMBt5mXFAL8DuC9SCK8FHo2NqhrzmM", "recommendations/3/context": "Arjun was senior to Casmiro but didn't manage Casmiro directly", "recommendations/3/date": "October 7, 2021", "recommendations/3/description": "Casmiro is an exceptional financial and all round leader. I would recommend any organization to have his expertise and experience part of their team. \nAlbeit we worked together way back in Dubai at The Sheraton Jumeirah, I’ve always cherished our professional interactions and would never ever hesitate to hire and or work with Casmiro again. \nHe always provided sound financial advice and more importantly always with a Partnership & Collaborative approach. \nIt’s been a privilege to see his career grow leaps and bounds. I wish him all the success possible. Always. ", "recommendations/3/name": "Casmiro Pereira", "recommendations/3/subtitle": "Director of Finance with Extensive Hospitality Experience 📈 End to End Hotel Development, Launch & Management Expertise 📈 Change Management, Governance & Continual Improvement across Individual Businesses & Groups", "recommendations/3/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/casmiro-pereira12121965/", "recommendations/3/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAADT140BDkKoCCCRp6KcNbJhcwAxEDXh4FQ", "recommendations/4/context": "Arjun managed Jessica M directly", "recommendations/4/date": "May 10, 2021", "recommendations/4/description": "“General Manager in the making” - that’s what I realized within the first 15 mins of connecting with Jessica back at The W Vieques during a task force assignment. \n\nJessica was the Dir of HSKP back then and I the task force General Manager. \n\nJessica always portrayed confidence in everything she did. She also demonstrated high level of integrity in what she was curious to learn and grow. I saw in her a caliber of executive who can drive accountability yet show understanding of her co workers and peers alike. \n\nI sincerely wish Jessica the very best as she climbs the corporate ladder towards her dream job and also pray our paths cross again to create more memorable experiences. ", "recommendations/4/name": "Jessica M Ferrer, MA", "recommendations/4/subtitle": "Complex Director of Human Resources", "recommendations/4/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/jessica-m-ferrer-ma-a8195727/", "recommendations/4/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAWoZkEBKrZpdBeCSCqdbdES_HYNZ5POs1A", "recommendations/5/context": "Arjun was senior to Sara but didn't manage Sara directly", "recommendations/5/date": "November 2, 2020", "recommendations/5/description": "\"Hire Sara if she has applied at your establishment\" - this is what I would tell any establishment's hiring manager where Sara's passion and journey takes her. \n\nI have had the distinct pleasure and privilege to serve Sara during our time at The Westin Calgary from 2015 to earlier this year 2020. I have always found Sara to be creative, resourceful, go-getter, pleasant and extremely courteous front line professional. She worked her way in the Front office team as a Guest Service Manager. Nothing was too much for Sara. \n\nWhile there are many stories of Sara's great feats that continue to inspire me one that will never be forgotten is how her passion in loyalty and commitment to her team made her bring creative roll out of Marriott Bonvoy loyalty program to all our Associates and Guests alike. She made it fun and managed to get the message across, never to be forgotten. \n\nI wish Sara all the best in her incredible journey ahead and cannot wait to how she keeps rising the corporate ladder towards her potential best. ", "recommendations/5/name": "Sara Tychkowsky", "recommendations/5/subtitle": "Rooms Division Manager at Basecamp Resorts", "recommendations/5/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/sara-tychkowsky-a70554a3/", "recommendations/5/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAABX44fQB5fGYhvp1eghQJtkbRsrwedjB5IM", "recommendations/6/context": "Arjun was senior to Laura but didn't manage Laura directly", "recommendations/6/date": "July 29, 2020", "recommendations/6/description": "“Hire Laura B, if she applies” - That’s how I would summarize having worked with this passionate Ops Leader. She doesn’t know the word ‘No’ when it comes to Guests or our fellow Co Workers. I’ve always heard amazing compliments from our Meeting planners about how Laura has been always one step ahead of them. Nothing beats that feedback. Lastly, she is incredibly resourceful which every employer needs. Miss working with her. All the best Laura ", "recommendations/6/name": "Laura Breuer", "recommendations/6/subtitle": "As a creative and detail-oriented Event Professional, I bring a passion for orchestrating seamless, memorable experiences while leading diverse, engaged teams with empathy and clarity.", "recommendations/6/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/hey-laura-breuer/", "recommendations/6/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAA8B7xoBgyP5NEZbvMu4KB11iCKh7AMCbjg", "recommendations/7/context": "Arjun was senior to Sam but didn't manage Sam directly", "recommendations/7/date": "April 1, 2020", "recommendations/7/description": "I’ve had the distinct pleasure to work with Sam Kim in Toronto. \n\nFrom the day we hired Sam, he was an utter delight to have on the team. \n\nSam is a fast learner and avid disciplined professional. \n\nI strongly recommend him to anyone who is looking to grow responsibly and an Organization that is looking to enhance its work culture by delivering on values and promises. ", "recommendations/7/name": "Sam Kim", "recommendations/7/subtitle": "General Manager, Embassy Suites by Hilton San Francisco Airport – Waterfront", "recommendations/7/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/samkim213/", "recommendations/7/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAxNr34B2-a67VXpzWvQ7Voq04GyntBG3Zo", "recommendations/8/date": "April 1, 2020", "recommendations/8/description": "With Komal on one’s team it’s like having a ‘resourceful, determined, grounded person’ on board. \n\nI’ve not had the pleasure nor privilege to have worked alongside Komal just yet but having worked across the globe in over 11 countries and diverse cultures, I can proudly say Komal is true professional and a master of her craft. \n\nKomal embodies the meaning of Team Player, Great Listener, Agile adapter, Concept developer & Flawless Executor. \n\nIn my various interactions with Komal, I’ve found her character to be super pleasant and easy to converse with. Qualities any Organization can make use of to build broken Culture or help thrive a great one. \n\nI wish Komal the very best and I’m excited to keep seeing her bridge the gap between her current self and the potential self. ", "recommendations/8/name": "Komal N.", "recommendations/8/subtitle": "Managing Director | Designer | Product Lead", "recommendations/8/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/komal-n/", "recommendations/8/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAoVsWoBcDyoxplEtBjxZyIPVjyJvwHZKSw", "recommendations/9/context": "Arjun was David's client", "recommendations/9/date": "February 14, 2020", "recommendations/9/description": "Albeit delayed but definitely not forgotten. \n\nDavid is an incredible source to anyone looking to simplify finance jargons in understandable terms that can help deliver returns, on top and bottom line, through people. \n\nOn behalf of Calgary Hotel Association, David delivered a memorable and engaged session on Financial Terms and deliverables that I know benefited our members in attendance. \n\nThank you David", "recommendations/9/name": "David Lund", "recommendations/9/subtitle": "🔷Author🔷Keynote Speaker🔷Hospitality Financial Mentoring & Workshops🔷Video Course🔷Podcast🔷Accounting Policy Manuals🔷 Executive Search", "recommendations/9/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/david-lund/", "recommendations/9/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAALGnfkBHts5MWCQhFoyy9XaL_QWQn8mq1g", "recommendations/10/context": "Arjun was Kamal's client", "recommendations/10/date": "February 14, 2020", "recommendations/10/description": "I’ve had the distinct and humble privilege to have traveled the world in my 30+ years spanning 11 countries and can without any doubt recommend the unmatchable services of Mr Sidhu. \n\nHe was responsive with care, efficient with purpose and determined with cause to help a family in their need hour  \n\nThank you Kamal for everything. Best wishes Arjun ", "recommendations/10/name": "Kamal Sidhu", "recommendations/10/subtitle": "Business Immigration Lead at Fragomen, Del Rey, Bernsen & Loewy LLP", "recommendations/10/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/kamal-sidhu-7500a749/", "recommendations/10/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAoobWwBn8gpEOwg2VM1QHZ5xUwBdye68gU", "recommendations/11/context": "Erin was Arjun's client", "recommendations/11/date": "October 14, 2017", "recommendations/11/description": "Very rarely do you get to come across True Professionals and Individuals whose sole purpose in providing you ‘unfiltered’ feedback is for you to  ‘learn and evolve’. \n\nErin has been that rare amazing person. \n\nThese very amazing Professionals Come back to your support as and when needed. It doesn’t get better than that. I wish Erin Well and whoever employs her should consider themselves very lucky. ", "recommendations/11/name": "Erin Gauthier", "recommendations/11/subtitle": "Medical Laboratory Technician at LifeLabs", "recommendations/11/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/erin-gauthier-a15810a5/", "recommendations/11/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAABZeBrEBW8SagPyUCBa6FvQ7DlPy6Z65AXE", "recommendations/12/context": "Arjun was senior to Sandeep but didn't manage Sandeep directly", "recommendations/12/date": "June 11, 2017", "recommendations/12/description": "I've had the privilege of working with Sandy during my time at the Sheraton Centre Toronto while she was at the Toronto Sales Metro Market. By no means Sandy's amazing journey thus far nor the commendable grooming, is to be underestimated nor limited to her various experiences. Having observed her in a group gathering and individual event setting, I can confirm with pleasure that Sandy is a seasoned Sales Professional ready for so much more. I wish her well, continually and look forward to working with her again somewhere. ", "recommendations/12/name": "Sandeep Cina", "recommendations/12/subtitle": "Director of Sales - Four Seasons Hotel Montreal", "recommendations/12/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/sandeepcina/", "recommendations/12/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAI0-xkB1kNbC5OIYz_CMQnahuUk5iVSHJI", "recommendations/13/context": "Arjun managed Mamta directly", "recommendations/13/date": "March 5, 2015", "recommendations/13/description": "Dear Reader (a Friend of Mamta or someone who is seriously considering to hire her), Hire her! Don't think twice. In Mamta you will find a dedicated Human (Relations) person who will go out of her way to make every connection a personal one. During my tenure at the Sheraton Udaipur, she was part of the conversion team and assisted in setting up Starwood Sheraton Brand Standards and Expectations. Her handwork and enthusiasm saw to it that we opened HOT with On Brand Associates. Under Challenging times, her best would come out and she would in her calmness, always offer alternatives and options. A quality that you don't find, almost like looking for a needle in a hay stack. I wish her well and she will be an incredible Asset to anyone. Best, Arjun Channa", "recommendations/13/name": "Mamta Sharma Ghadiali", "recommendations/13/subtitle": "Strategic Partner | HR Professional | Mentor | Learner | Director - HR, Emotional Well-being Therapist", "recommendations/13/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/mamta-sharma-ghadiali/", "recommendations/13/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAZkvIcBbg0xU3A7nANx4gDX2V99PKGoilc", "recommendations/14/context": "Arjun managed Mohammed directly", "recommendations/14/date": "March 3, 2015", "recommendations/14/description": "\"Mohammed Sharik is a go-getter and a relentless Sales Force embedded in One, who will stop at nothing until he achieves what is required for the Organisation. During my tenure as GM of the Sheraton in Udaipur, Mohammed excelled in his Sales targets often and with special emphasis on the MICE market which was important for Udaipur. I wish him all the luck possible\"", "recommendations/14/name": "Mohammed Shariq", "recommendations/14/subtitle": "Director-Ybrant Hospitality", "recommendations/14/url": "https://www.linkedin.com/in/mohammedsharik/", "recommendations/14/urn": "urn:li:fsd_profile:ACoAAAs8ubgB7dMWFY0E5kAyeYRG4St_z09rADk", "recommendations/15/context": "Arjun worked with Gurnoor on the same team", "recommendations/15/date": "July 7, 2011", "recommendations/15/description": "Though I have not known Gurnoor in terms of quantitative time having worked with her just under a year, the experience has been nothing les